SIMPLE: depatriate
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Depatriate
<hw>De*pa"tri*ate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t. & i.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>de-</ets> + <ets>patria</ets> one's country.]</ety> <def>To
withdraw, or cause to withdraw, from one's country; to banish.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A subject born in any state⟦br⟧
May, if he please, <qex>depatriate</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Mason.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Depauperate</ent>⟦br⟧
